AI Coding & Business Tutor
An interactive, browser-based application designed to help interns and junior developers practice their skills in Python, SQL, and Business Acumen. This tool uses the Google Gemini API to generate an endless supply of questions and provide instant, detailed feedback on user-submitted answers.

âœ¨ Features
Multiple Domains: Practice questions across three key areas:

Python: Algorithmic and data science questions with an in-browser code execution environment powered by Pyodide.

SQL: Realistic database scenarios with sample data and expected outputs.

Business Development: "Unseen" case studies and "Seen" passage comprehension questions to build business acumen.

Dynamic Question Generation: Select a domain, difficulty level (Easy, Medium, Hard), and specific topics to get a tailored question.

AI-Powered Feedback: Submit your answer to get an instant evaluation on correctness, along with a detailed analysis and an optimal solution.

Interactive Environment:

In-browser Python code execution to test your solution before submitting.

An advanced code editor (CodeMirror) with syntax highlighting.

Interactive "Get a Hint" and "Next Challenge" features to guide the learning process.

No Backend Required: The entire application runs in the browser, making it easy to deploy on any static hosting service.

ðŸš€ Tech Stack
Frontend: HTML, Tailwind CSS, Vanilla JavaScript

Code Editor: CodeMirror

Python Execution: Pyodide

AI Model: Google Gemini API (gemini-2.5-flash-lite)

ðŸ”§ Setup & Usage
Get an API Key:

Go to Google AI Studio.

Click on "Get API key" and then "Create API key in new project".

Copy the generated API key.

Run Locally:

Save the index.html file to your computer.

Open the file in a modern web browser (like Chrome, Firefox, or Edge).

Start Practicing:

Paste your API key into the input field and click "Set Key".

Choose a domain, difficulty, and topic to get started!
